Hi @MitchFuchs ,

I experienced the same issue with the newest 2.3rc1. I tried to launch it on a gpu node on  CentOS 8.4.2105.

I fixed this issue by uninstalling opencv-python with pip and re-installing the headless version with conda. I am running into other issues though, but I briefly was able to use the GUI to label images, which make me think this solution is valid

`pip uninstall opencv-python`
`conda install -c fastai opencv-python-headless`

hi @MitchFuchs seems you have some issues here with CUDA; what do you have installed? See: https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/51080

Also after upgrading CUDA for latest, please run: `pip install --upgrade --force-reinstall 'deeplabcut[gui,tf]'==2.3rc2`

Thanks @MMathisLab! 

I confirm that 

`pip install --upgrade --force-reinstall 'deeplabcut[gui,tf]'==2.3rc2`

followed by 

`pip install torch==1.7.1+cu110 torchvision==0.8.2+cu110 torchaudio===0.7.2 -f https://download.pytorch.org/whl/torch_stable.html`

solves the issue (I use CUDA 11.0).  

The command 

`python -m deeplabcut`

successfully lanches the GUI

Best, 
Mitch.

### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

`python -m deeplabcut` fails to launch GUI with DLC 2.3.0. If matplotlib is installed in same environment. 

### Operating System

Ubuntu 20.04
CUDA 11.4

### DeepLabCut version

dlc version 2.3.0

### DeepLabCut mode

single animal

### Device type

NVIDIA GeForce GT 710/NVIDIA A100

### Steps To Reproduce

Create the dlc_test.yaml
```
name: dlc_test
channels:
  - conda-forge
  - defaults
  - pytorch
dependencies:
  - python>=3.8, <3.10
  - pip>=20.2.*
  - matplotlib
  - pytorch<1.12.0
  - torchvision
  - torchaudio
  - cudatoolkit=11.3
  - tensorflow>=2.0
  - numba>=0.48.0
  - pip:
    - "deeplabcut[gui]"
```

Run:
`mamba env create -f dlc_test.yaml`
`python -m deeplabcut`

It looks like the install of pyqt and pyqt5-sip interfere with use of pyside6.

I attempted the fix mentioned in #2009:
`pip install torch==1.7.1+cu110 torchvision==0.8.2+cu110 torchaudio===0.7.2 -f https://download.pytorch.org/whl/torch_stable.html`
But the issue remains.

Hi @jeylau, I seemingly am having the same issue (After following the suggestion in #2118 to only use the DLC conda environment with deeplabcut[tf,gui], although I changed the name to DEEPLABCUT-test to avoid conflicts). I run: ``` conda env create -f DEEPLABCUT-test.yaml conda activate DEEPLABCUT-test python -m deeplabcut ``` and it crashes here. I've tried the following as suggested previously in this issue, which doesn't change the error: ``` pip uninstall opencv-python pip install opencv-python-headless ``` I have also tried the suggestions [here](https://forum.qt.io/topic/111553/solved-qt-qpa-plugin-could-not-find-the-qt-platform-plugin-xcb-in/2) to no avail. I'm running this on Ubuntu 20.04 with a NVIDIA GeForce GT 710 GPU and CUDA 11.4 While I can continue using DLC <2.3 I was hoping to incorporate the bug fix from #2036.
